FBIS4-13153 "drnes074_s_94014" FBIS-NES-94-074 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 Iran Velayati Receives Vietnam's Deputy Foreign Minister Velayati Receives Vietnam's Deputy Foreign Minister LD1504155894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in English 1130 GMT 15 Apr 94 LD1504155894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran English BFN [Text] Vietnam's deputy foreign minister today in a meeting with Dr. Velayati in Tehran called for the expansion of cooperation in international circles and organizations. Nguyen Dy Niem, who brought the Vietnamese president's message to Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani, in the meeting expressed hope that with the Vietnamese president's imminent visit to Iran, ties between the two countries will be further strengthened. The Islamic Republic of Iran's foreign minister, Dr. Velayati, during the meeting pointed to the historical record of the Vietnamese combats against occupiers and said: The Islamic Republic of Iran places great significance on Vietnam. Expressing Iran's readiness for hosting the Vietnamese president, Mr. Velayati said he is hopeful that the visit will have good foreign policy results for expanding the two countries' ties.
